This paper belongs to the computer vision (CV) field as it deals with generating realistic future frames. The use of conditional generative adversarial networks (GANs) and appearance and motion information suggests that it may also fall under the machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) sub-categories. The evaluation of the model using facial expression and human action datasets suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (GR) and multimedia (MM) sub-categories.
